com.mot.iden.zip
Class ZipInputStream

java.lang.Object
  java.io.InputStream
      com.mot.iden.zip.FilterInputStream
          com.mot.iden.zip.InflaterInputStream
              com.mot.iden.zip.ZipInputStream
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.mot.iden.zip.ZipConstants
public class ZipInputStream
extends InflaterInputStream
implements com.mot.iden.zip.ZipConstants

This class implements an input stream filter for reading files in the ZIP file format. Includes support for both compressed and uncompressed entries.

Constructor Detail

ZipInputStream

public ZipInputStream(java.io.InputStream in)
Creates a new ZIP input stream. This method will allocate memory. For J2ME programming, due to the limitation of Java heap, it is better to relase the memory with close() if calling the method. Please do not repeat calling the method many times without release.

Parameters:
in - the actual input stream

available

public int available()
              throws java.io.IOException
Returns 0 after EOF has reached for the current entry data, otherwise always return 1.

Programs should not count on this method to return the actual number of bytes that could be read without blocking.

Overrides:
available in class InflaterInputStream
Returns:
1 before EOF and 0 after EOF has reached for current entry.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
